R. W. Harrison (harrison@calvin.jci.tju.edu) wrote:
: Would  DESinv( RN xor DES( M,key) ,key) be resonable?  RN is either

RSA's DESX algorithm is similar, but faster:

DESX(M,k1,k2,k3) = k1 xor (DES(M xor k3), k2)

DESX is used in commercial products, so obviously the
cryptographers at RSADSI have faith in it.

A free implementation of DESX can be found at ripem.msu.edu.
See GETTING_ACCESS.
/mrr
